added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Campfire Stories
added.description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

added.title: Pepo The Pumpkinman
added.description: A magic hat brings the Titans' pumpkinman to life, but they have to figure out how to keep Pepo from rotting.

added.title: High Baby Fashion
added.description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

added.title: Teddi Bear
added.description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

added.title: A Gross Worm
added.description: The Bears help Unica return an endangered alien worm to its home.

added.title: A Real Crayon
added.description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

added.title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
added.description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

added.title: Dude Where's Macaw
added.description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

added.title: Protein Titans 2
added.description: When a mega-successful video game company tries to buy an old algorithm from Velma and convince her to work for them in San Francisco, the gang becomes embroiled in the mystery of a video game villain who has seemingly come to life, the Ghost Chef.

added.title: World of Witchcraft
added.description: The gang goes to Salem, Massachusetts for a historical festival, only to discover history repeating itself as a demon has been set loose on the town, supposedly summoned by a witch as revenge for the infamous 17th Century Salem Witch Trials. As the Mayor stirs up fear and paranoia, the whole town goes witch hunt crazy and it's not long before suspicions fall on the gang, in particular, Daphne, who feels empathy for the eccentric, free spirited women accused of witchcraft 350 years ago.

added.title: Professor Huh? Part 1
added.description: Fred and the gang are called in to help with a mystery involving a figure from Fred's past, Professor Huh? Fred discovers, Rose, his old childhood friend, with whom he learned mystery solving until they had a falling out, has also arrived with her gang. The race to see which gang could solve the mystery first is on, as the rest of the gang learns there's more to this story than meets the eye and Fred's interest in finding Professor Huh? is as personal as it gets.

added.title: Professor Huh? Part 6 3/4
added.description: Fred and the gang are called in to help with a mystery involving a figure from Fred's past, Professor Huh? Fred discovers, Rose, his old childhood friend, with whom he learned mystery solving until they had a falling out, has also arrived with her gang. The race to see which gang could solve the mystery first is on, as the rest of the gang learns there's more to this story than meets the eye and Fred's interest in finding Professor Huh? is as personal as it gets.

added.title: Pizza O'Possum's/The Curse of Half-Beard's Booty
added.description: Pizza O'Possum's: Shaggy drags the gang to a childhood arcade where he's determined to finally collect enough tickets to win the prize he's wanted since he was a boy. Unfortunately, the animatronic mascot of the place has apparently come to life and has other ideas./The Curse of Half-Beard's Booty: At a seafood restaurant, the gang comes across Captain Cutler, who Fred is determined to catch once and for all. Cutler explains that he's turned over a new leaf and opened up this restaurant to earn an honest living. Unfortunately, the ghost of a legendary pirate, Half-Beard, has been scaring away his customers. Fred and Cutler form an uneasy alliance as he joins the gang on a treasure hunt at Double-Cross Cove where Half-Beard's treasure is supposedly buried.

added.title: Dance Matron of Mayhem!
added.description: When famous dancer Maddie Ziegler wins an old, haunted dance studio in a competition, she asks her friend Daphne Blake and her mystery solving friends to help her investigate the place. They soon run afoul of the ghost of Madame Zobrinsky, famous original owner of the dance studio in question. Does Maddie have the dance skills to teach our Shaggy and Scooby to be graceful and light on their feet?

added.title: The Wedding Witch of Wainsly Hall!
added.description: Scooby and our gang of mystery solving teens have been invited by famous comedian Jeff Foxworthy to help him move an old mansion that he's just purchased. But, when they find out the mansion is haunted by the ghost of an old witch, this Southern-fried mystery takes a dramatic turn. Can our gang help Mr. Foxworthy save this mansion from destruction?

added.title: A Run Cycle Through Time!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang accept an invitation from famous actor Malcolm McDowell to take an exploratory trip through time, they find themselves actually traveling into the future. What follows is a strange mystery involving a Malcolm from the future who keeps trying to stop them going any further. Can our gang get to the bottom of this time traveling mystery and save Mr. McDowell from his own invention?

added.title: I Put a Hex on You!
added.description: When Daphne's makeup vlog lands her as the prime consultant to the famous rock band, the Hex Girls, our gang find themselves embroiled in a rockin' mystery involving a cursed guitar that seems to control people's minds. Can our heroes help right this upside-down wrong in time for the band to truly rock for a packed stadium?

added.title: The High School Wolfman's Musical Lament!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang teams up with famous actor Christian Slater, they find themselves embroiled in a musical mystery full of songs, clues and crazy chases. Christian's classmates are having a redo prom to make up for the one they were deprived of when a horrible Wolfman appeared all those years ago. The Wolfman is making a mysterious reappearance at this do-over prom threatening to not only destroy the prom yet again but the lives of all concerned!

added.title: Scooby's Night with a Frozen Fright
added.description: Shaggy and Scooby hook a frozen caveman and present the chilly artifact to Oceanland. But the creature is mysteriously thawed out and goes on a rampage.

added.title: Haunted House Hang-Up
added.description: The gang investigates a haunted southern mansion when the Mystery Machine overheats and strands them nearby.

added.title: A Tiki Scare Is No Fair
added.description: A Hawaiian vacation turns into another investigation when Scooby and Shaggy are threatened by a witch doctor.

added.title: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Werewolf
added.description: The gang goes camping and stumbles across a lonely graveyard and an empty tomb, whose missing inhabitant was suspected of being a werewolf.

added.title: Don't Fool with a Phantom
added.description: A phantom interrupts Shaggy and Scooby's performance on a TV dance show.

added.title: Nightmare in Red
added.description: Our heroes allow themselves to be hypnotized so that they can enter the dreamworld.

added.title: Dark Night of the Hunters
added.description: Searching for the Heart of the Jaguar, the Mystery Incorporated gang heads down south of the border.

added.title: Gates of Gloom
added.description: Professor Pericles and what's left of his Mystery Incorporated are looking for the entrance into the caverns, where the cursed treasure and the Evil Entity are buried.

added.title: Through the Curtain
added.description: Traveling through the underground caverns, our heroes trail Pericles and company.

added.title: Come Undone
added.description: It's the end of the world! And our heroes must work together to ultimately realize their love for each other is the true Heart of the Jaguar.

added.title: The Brain of Evil
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to recapture something they lost.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park VI
added.description: In Regular Show's sixth installment of "Terror Tales," the guys gather in the house on the Dome and tell scary Halloween stories just like ol' times, only this Halloween, the stories have an extra terrifying, science fiction twist.

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
added.description: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

added.title: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
added.description: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

added.title: Killer Bed/Jacked Up-O-Lantern
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: Creepy Doll/Death Metal Crash Pit
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby discover an old Victorian Doll that Pop's has not played with or seen since he was a child and unwittingly unleash its pent up rage against him.  Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to crash an old RV into a pit, but it's haunted by an 80s death metal band.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Phased and Confused
added.description: When members of the Justice League are affected by the Phantom Zone ray and become phantom-like, their only hope for freedom is to somehow get a message to Booster Gold.

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: A New Dawn
added.description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Garden of Evil
added.description: Poison Ivy takes control of Swamp Thing using his vegetative powers to overwhelm Gotham with dangerous plants.

added.title: All Aboard the Space Train
added.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

added.title: Time Out
added.description: Batman must team up with Booster Gold when an inter-demoniacal alien creature starts eating up time literally.

added.title: The Fatal Fare
added.description: Space Cabbie inadvertently learns about a great threat to the Justice League when one of his passengers turns out to be Darkseid.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
added.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.
